results.name: a(n) = largest m such that 1, 2, ..., m divide n-th Fibonacci number; a(n) = A055874(A000045(n)).
comment: It seems that the records occur at the positions given by A233283: 1, 3, 12, 60, 120, 840, 2520, 12600, ...
The corresponding record values begin as 1, 2, 4, 6, 12, 16, 24, 36, ... (maybe A007416?).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..12600
xref: Differs from A233285 for the first time at n=120, where a(120)=12, while A233285(120)=7.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Dec 12 2013
